{"questionId":"26440","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Leo is investigating whether a six-sided die is fair. He rolls the die <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math> times and records the&nbsp;observed frequencies in the following table:</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/ef136bc70fb66eaac3e9e958112f9dcce10d5359.png\"></p>\n<p>Leo carries out a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>χ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> goodness of fit test at a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math> significance level.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the degrees of freedom.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26440","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.7b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the degrees of freedom.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}